{"id":14882020,"mediaExerciseId":"9f873a33-b9a0-4bba-b9a5-101165e6ddf2","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"27","chapterTitle":"Leasing","groupId":612532,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":909,"solutions":[{"id":6504744,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The purpose of this assignment is to set out the reasons why the airline might prefer to lease the aircraft rather than purchase it.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"China Southern has several options for financing the new assets. It could buy them directly from the manufacturer (Boeing) through a loan probably. On the other hand, it could lease the asset as an alternative form of financing. \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, ***what would be the positive consequences of leasing assets instead of buying them?***\n\n- The reduction of taxes imposed on the company by opting for leasing.\n\n- Leasing can reduce uncertainty about the value of the asset at the end of its lease. Leasing is a way in which an asset can be used without the risk of not knowing what the residual value of the asset will be. This risk is assumed by the lessor.\n\n- Leasing can result in lower transaction costs than purchasing the asset.\n\n- The opportunity to obtain a lease is less restrictive than obtaining a loan to acquire the asset.  \n\n- The lease may encumber fewer assets than secured loans.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3729939e-cb95-4d1a-a548-b36f8944ad8b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jor